Videos

The tuition industry is very competitive in Singapore these days and with the help of technology, we believe you can stand out from the rest of your competitors to secure a job.

We have worked with thousands of profiles since our inception, and we realised tutors who had recorded a short introduction of themselves tend to get selected than their peers who do not.

Your introductory video will not be published to the public but only made available whenever we send your profile to our potential clients to review.

Your personal data is always protected, as a temporary URL link will be sent to the client for viewing and it will expire in 72 hours.

For more information about our privacy policy, you may view it here.

While recording your own introductory video, please remember to keep it short and to the point.

You may use the below guidelines to record your introduction.

  • Describe your name, current occupation and personality
  • Years of teaching experience
  • Total number of students taught
  • Levels & subjects that you have taught
  • The improvements that your students have made
  • Other achievements/experience (Relief teaching, a tutor in a tuition centre, Dean's list, scholarship, public speaking etc.)
  • Why you are the best person for the job?
